  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ 425°F/ Gas 7</p><p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Add the <strong>chicken breast fillets </strong>to a bowl with the<strong> smoked paprika</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and mix until coated</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1597826112081-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1597826112081-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1597826112081-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1597826112081-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1597826112081-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based dry pan (preferably non-stick) with a matching lid over a high heat</p><p>Add the <strong>coated chicken</strong> and cook for 2 min on each side, then add 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until cooked through</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1597826117178-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1597826117178-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1597826117178-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1597826117178-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1597826117178-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut the <strong>sweet potatoes</strong> (skins on) into wedges</p><p>Add the <strong>wedges</strong> to a large baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until the wedges are tender and starting to crisp</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1597826122574-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1597826122574-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1597826122574-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1597826122574-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1597826122574-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop the <strong>coriander </strong>finely, including the stalks</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>chopped coriander</strong>,<strong> garlic</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!),<strong> red wine vinegar </strong>and 3 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[6 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil </strong>to a bowl</p><p>Season generously with<strong> salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up – this is your<strong> chimichurri sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1597826127268-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1597826127268-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1597826127268-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1597826127268-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1597826127268-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is cooked, remove the pan from the heat and shred apart using two forks – this technique is known as 'pulling'</p><p>Drain and pat the <strong>mozzarella</strong> dry with kitchen paper (squeeze as much liquid out as you can)</p><p>Tear the <strong>drained mozzarella</strong> into rough, bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1597826133287-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1597826133287-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1597826133287-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1597826133287-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1597826133287-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>torn</strong> <strong>mozzarella</strong> to the pan and mix it with the <strong>shredded chicken</strong></p><p>Divide the<strong> chicken & mozzarella mixture </strong>between the <strong>tortilla wraps</strong>, covering only half</p><p>Fold each tortilla over and press down firmly so you're left with 6 <span class=\"text-danger\">[12]</span> half moon-shaped sandwiches – these are your <strong>chicken</strong> <strong>quesadillas</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1597826141588-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1597826141588-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1597826141588-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1597826141588-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1597826141588-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> chicken quesadillas </strong>to a baking tray (or two!)</p><p>Place a second baking tray (or the tray of sweet potato wedges!) on top to weigh them down slightly</p><p>Put the <strong>stacked baking trays</strong> in the oven for 10-12 min or until the quesadillas are slightly browned and the cheese has melted</p>",
